747
01:02:34,785 --> 01:02:38,246
But the whole area is an absolute
monument to consumerism.

748
01:02:38,246 --> 01:02:40,239
All we can do is hope.

749
01:02:40,248 --> 01:02:42,287
Check all the floors
including the basement.

750
01:02:49,507 --> 01:02:52,843
<i>Isn't that a scary noise?</i>

751
01:02:52,843 --> 01:02:55,302
Wanna hear it again?

752
01:02:55,303 --> 01:02:57,968
<i>Gosh, the suspense
is killing me.</i>

753
01:03:00,058 --> 01:03:01,551
Let's do it again.

754
01:03:04,019 --> 01:03:06,308
<i>An E-ticket attraction.</i>

755
01:03:06,313 --> 01:03:07,896
Let's do it again.

756
01:03:11,317 --> 01:03:12,982
<i>Now, wait a minute.</i>

757
01:03:12,986 --> 01:03:16,947
I don't think there's really
a bullet in here.

758
01:03:16,947 --> 01:03:20,863
No, now see there, it's loaded.

759
01:03:20,867 --> 01:03:24,078
I just needed to be
a little more patient.

760
01:03:24,079 --> 01:03:27,243
I think this is it, girls.
I really do.

761
01:03:51,477 --> 01:03:54,972
Uh... we're not with these guys.

762
01:03:54,981 --> 01:03:57,351
<i>Really, like,
we just met 'em an hour ago.</i>

763
01:03:58,526 --> 01:04:01,770
I mean,
look at this stuff that we have.

764
01:04:01,778 --> 01:04:03,146
Look at this skirt...

765
01:04:03,155 --> 01:04:04,523
<i>It's ironic.</i>

766
01:04:04,531 --> 01:04:07,696
<i>Of all the great minds of the world,
all the great intellects,</i>

767
01:04:07,701 --> 01:04:09,444
<i>who should survive?</i>

768
01:04:09,452 --> 01:04:11,115
<i>Or almost survive.</i>

769
01:04:12,538 --> 01:04:14,952
<i>I don't have to see the result
of the blood test.</i>

770
01:04:15,791 --> 01:04:17,749
I can guess what they say
about that one.

771
01:04:21,629 --> 01:04:22,837
You're right.

772
01:04:23,965 --> 01:04:25,799
It would be senseless
to take her back.

773
01:04:25,800 --> 01:04:28,168
<i>Look, I'll stay
and take care of it.</i>

774
01:04:28,177 --> 01:04:31,547
Then if this Hector person shows up,
I can run tests on him too.

775
01:04:32,306 --> 01:04:34,970
Of course, uh, it would be
out of the question

776
01:04:34,974 --> 01:04:36,889
to let you remain
by yourself.

777
01:04:37,853 --> 01:04:39,311
I'll stay here with you.

778
01:04:59,955 --> 01:05:03,291
<i>Listen, thanks
for suggesting that I wait for Hector.</i>

779
01:05:03,292 --> 01:05:05,125
<i>I mean, I know Reggie'll
probably get him,</i>

780
01:05:05,126 --> 01:05:06,915
<i>but I'd like to have
a shot at it.</i>

781
01:05:07,545 --> 01:05:09,538
<i>Samantha,
I need you to lie down.</i>

782
01:05:10,423 --> 01:05:12,507
Hector's not exactly
a fox, but...

783
01:05:13,468 --> 01:05:16,803
considering what's left,
he's not bad.

784
01:05:16,803 --> 01:05:18,716
He sounds cute.

785
01:05:18,721 --> 01:05:19,884
Is he coming back?

786
01:05:19,889 --> 01:05:21,007
Yeah.

787
01:05:21,475 --> 01:05:24,060
<i>But we should wait for him
at the radio station.</i>

788
01:05:25,020 --> 01:05:26,887
<i>That's where he'll go.</i>

789
01:05:26,896 --> 01:05:28,059
<i>What's that?</i>

790
01:05:29,189 --> 01:05:31,434
Um, I'm gonna give
you something.

791
01:05:31,442 --> 01:05:33,309
For what?

792
01:05:33,318 --> 01:05:37,689
Well, your skin's been
a little irritated.

793
01:05:37,697 --> 01:05:39,280
Yeah, a rash.

794
01:05:39,281 --> 01:05:43,368
It could be a rash, but it could also
be something else.

795
01:05:43,369 --> 01:05:44,907
It's one of the main
symptoms of--

796
01:05:44,912 --> 01:05:46,120
The comet, no.

797
01:05:46,121 --> 01:05:50,958
See, I always get rashes like,
when I have a fight with Doris

798
01:05:50,959 --> 01:05:52,918
or I break up with a boyfriend.

799
01:05:52,919 --> 01:05:54,082
It's nerves, and you know,

800
01:05:54,087 --> 01:05:56,421
the way things have been going
around here lately,

801
01:05:56,421 --> 01:05:58,881
I'm surprised I don't look
like strawberry Jell-O.

802
01:06:00,926 --> 01:06:05,468
But if I do have that stuff,
this'll get rid of it, right?

803
01:06:07,265 --> 01:06:09,679
- Yeah.
- God, you had me worried.

804
01:06:11,560 --> 01:06:12,722
Don't worry.

805
01:06:13,645 --> 01:06:15,105
Just a pinch, now.

806
01:06:15,981 --> 01:06:17,144
Ow!

807
01:06:21,903 --> 01:06:24,863
So you guys are like,
geniuses, right?

808
01:06:25,990 --> 01:06:29,280
Yeah, I thought so.

809
01:06:36,581 --> 01:06:39,416
We have a couple
of geniuses at my school.

810
01:06:39,418 --> 01:06:41,208
Yeah?

811
01:06:41,212 --> 01:06:44,957
Yeah, they're both wimps.

812
01:07:01,730 --> 01:07:03,018
Is, uh...

813
01:07:04,774 --> 01:07:06,062
Is that it?

814
01:07:08,277 --> 01:07:10,691
What did you want me
to do, Oscar?

815
01:07:10,696 --> 01:07:12,735
Take her out back
and shoot her in the head?

816
01:07:14,366 --> 01:07:18,532
I simply meant
I was glad it was... painless.

817
01:07:19,120 --> 01:07:22,081
I don't think
we have to stay around.

818
01:07:23,582 --> 01:07:25,201
She didn't think
that he was coming back.

819
01:07:26,626 --> 01:07:28,665
I feel we can wait.

820
01:07:29,588 --> 01:07:30,955
But, uh...

821
01:07:31,965 --> 01:07:36,302
I-- I feel the radio station is
the more logical place.

822
01:07:39,138 --> 01:07:44,726
Listen, Oscar, you were right about
the condition being progressive.

823
01:07:44,726 --> 01:07:49,348
But it is also accelerating,
apparently.

824
01:07:49,356 --> 01:07:51,565
We don't have weeks.

825
01:07:51,565 --> 01:07:53,058
We have maybe hours.

826
01:07:53,067 --> 01:07:54,435
<i>I don't know.</i>

827
01:07:54,443 --> 01:07:55,686
We have a commitment.

828
01:07:55,694 --> 01:07:58,313
But I do know, I don't have
enough to debate the issue.

829
01:07:58,322 --> 01:08:02,658
I am not going to be a party
to taking anybody else back.

830
01:08:02,658 --> 01:08:04,195
You have to live up to it.

831
01:08:05,995 --> 01:08:08,489
What do you expect
me to do, Oscar?

832
01:08:08,498 --> 01:08:10,207
Go for my gun?

833
01:08:11,333 --> 01:08:12,541
Of course not.

834
01:08:52,620 --> 01:08:54,783
<i>Hey, it's 450 FM in the PM.</i>

835
01:08:54,788 --> 01:08:57,998
<i>I'm Steve LaBeau, and you're listening
to 50,000 watts of rock and roll</i>

836
01:08:57,998 --> 01:09:00,618
<i>at tower of power
over the City of Angels.</i>

837
01:09:20,727 --> 01:09:22,720
Reggie?

838
01:09:22,729 --> 01:09:24,222
Merry Christmas.

839
01:09:28,734 --> 01:09:29,977
Reggie?

840
01:09:36,659 --> 01:09:37,867
Samantha?

841
01:09:43,665 --> 01:09:46,078
- Hi.
- Hm.

842
01:09:46,083 --> 01:09:47,247
Hi.

843
01:09:50,337 --> 01:09:53,752
Did you happen to see
two girls runnin' around here?

844
01:09:53,756 --> 01:09:55,294
One's a cheerleader.

845
01:09:56,384 --> 01:09:59,345
I'm not thinking straight.

846
01:09:59,345 --> 01:10:02,464
I wrote everything down, but...

847
01:10:02,473 --> 01:10:03,886
I think I misspelled it.

848
01:10:03,891 --> 01:10:05,429
That pad on the table.

849
01:10:08,103 --> 01:10:09,687
You need this?

850
01:10:09,688 --> 01:10:11,352
No, thanks, I have one.

851
01:10:13,733 --> 01:10:16,068
Seems to be the perfect
Christmas gift this year.

852
01:10:18,404 --> 01:10:19,897
I'm gonna miss Christmas.

853
01:10:21,407 --> 01:10:22,774
Permanently.

854
01:10:25,409 --> 01:10:30,156
<i>I want you to know that I thought
they were talking hypothetically.</i>

855
01:10:30,164 --> 01:10:32,453
Until they found
the first survivors.

856
01:10:32,458 --> 01:10:33,917
Then they really did it.

857
01:10:36,836 --> 01:10:38,921
Some of those survivors
were just kids.

858
01:10:38,922 --> 01:10:41,633
Hey, wait a minute.
What's all this about blood?

859
01:10:45,136 --> 01:10:47,094
They think they can
generate a serum.

860
01:10:48,305 --> 01:10:49,513
A serum?

861
01:10:49,515 --> 01:10:53,477
<i>We were exposed.
Not a lot. Just enough.</i>

862
01:10:54,561 --> 01:10:57,225
They left the ventilating
ducts wide open.

863
01:10:57,230 --> 01:10:59,064
The fans going.

864
01:10:59,065 --> 01:11:01,309
Very scientific.

865
01:11:01,317 --> 01:11:02,934
Very stupid.

866
01:11:05,321 --> 01:11:07,234
In 36 hours

867
01:11:08,782 --> 01:11:12,868
you will be able to vacuum up
the last of them up from the carpet.

868
01:11:15,330 --> 01:11:18,073
<i>Hey, you know what?</i>

869
01:11:20,458 --> 01:11:22,793
She was right.

870
01:11:22,794 --> 01:11:24,253
You are cute.

871
01:11:25,965 --> 01:11:27,753
Santa Claus.

872
01:11:40,268 --> 01:11:41,431
Hey.

873
01:11:59,868 --> 01:12:01,577
<i>Have you ever had hepatitis?</i>

874
01:12:01,579 --> 01:12:03,321
Darn tags.

875
01:12:03,329 --> 01:12:04,742
Do you have a pair of scissors?

876
01:12:06,000 --> 01:12:07,162
No.

877
01:12:07,166 --> 01:12:08,409
Have you ever had hepatitis?

878
01:12:11,713 --> 01:12:13,047
Cute kids.

879
01:12:13,797 --> 01:12:15,040
<i>They a part of you guys?</i>

880
01:12:15,799 --> 01:12:16,882
<i>No.</i>

881
01:12:17,759 --> 01:12:20,378
They're survivors
just like you are.

882
01:12:20,387 --> 01:12:21,630
Neat girl, huh?

883
01:12:21,638 --> 01:12:23,926
If you like the type.

884
01:12:23,931 --> 01:12:25,640
Come on, kids,
come with me.

885
01:12:28,311 --> 01:12:29,804
<i>Have you ever had hepatitis?</i>

886
01:12:33,482 --> 01:12:36,225
No, I had mono once, though.

887
01:12:36,234 --> 01:12:38,603
Caught if from this guy
named Randy Sharp.

888
01:12:39,529 --> 01:12:40,566
Anemia?

889
01:12:40,988 --> 01:12:42,402
No.

890
01:12:42,407 --> 01:12:44,320
<i>- Are you pregnant?
- Nope.</i>

891
01:12:44,325 --> 01:12:45,659
Thought I was once, though.

892
01:12:47,577 --> 01:12:48,820
That's not important.

893
01:12:48,828 --> 01:12:51,072
That's what you think.

894
01:12:51,080 --> 01:12:53,245
That was the longest
three weeks of my life.

895
01:12:59,046 --> 01:13:00,460
You know I can't remember.

896
01:13:00,465 --> 01:13:03,299
How much blood were we expected
to get from these people?

897
01:13:03,842 --> 01:13:08,508
- Uh, 300 ccs, yes, that's it.
- That can't be right.

898
01:13:08,512 --> 01:13:11,848
If we draw 300 ccs a day,
they'll expire altogether.

899
01:13:11,849 --> 01:13:15,595
<i>No, I don't think so, now that
we've terminated brain functions.</i>

900
01:13:15,603 --> 01:13:17,346
I mean, they're brain dead.

901
01:13:17,355 --> 01:13:20,098
All they can do now
is manufacture blood.

902
01:13:21,607 --> 01:13:23,351
Well, maybe.

903
01:13:24,860 --> 01:13:28,651
Well, we aren't going to get anything
like 300 ccs out of those children.

904
01:13:28,656 --> 01:13:30,570
<i>No, but we will
out of that teenager.</i>

905
01:13:30,574 --> 01:13:32,692
I hope she's just
as healthy as she looks.

906
01:13:32,700 --> 01:13:34,944
Boy, did you see her hair?

907
01:13:34,952 --> 01:13:37,322
What I've give
to have hair like that.

908
01:13:39,040 --> 01:13:40,283
What is this place?

909
01:13:42,084 --> 01:13:43,998
Do you have diabetes?

910
01:13:44,002 --> 01:13:46,041
I mean, is this
some sort of, I don't know,

911
01:13:46,046 --> 01:13:47,630
underground hospital,
or what?

912
01:13:50,926 --> 01:13:52,759
You're a very strong willed
young lady.

913
01:13:54,095 --> 01:13:55,383
Cancer.

914
01:13:56,305 --> 01:13:57,888
You have cancer?

915
01:13:57,889 --> 01:14:00,259
No, I am a Cancer.

916
01:14:00,267 --> 01:14:03,636
I just want to know where I am
and what I'm doing here.

917
01:14:16,155 --> 01:14:18,319
<i>Oops.</i>

918
01:14:18,324 --> 01:14:20,785
Oh, gosh, uh, could you hand me
that arterial--

919
01:14:20,786 --> 01:14:21,743
Got it.

920
01:14:29,334 --> 01:14:32,750
Well, it's up
to the respirators now.

921
01:14:32,754 --> 01:14:34,292
Why don't we prep
the children?

922
01:14:34,297 --> 01:14:37,541
When we're finished with them,
we can start on that girl.

923
01:14:37,550 --> 01:14:39,168
They're so cute.

924
01:14:39,176 --> 01:14:40,384
I love working with kids.

925
01:14:41,053 --> 01:14:44,093
<i>Yeah.
Oh, don't forget the lights.</i>

926
01:14:48,726 --> 01:14:50,595
Are you taking any medication?

927
01:14:56,775 --> 01:15:00,440
Have you had any medication
within the last 24 hours?

928
01:15:02,739 --> 01:15:04,357
Where's my sister?

929
01:15:08,494 --> 01:15:10,703
Dr. Carter,
may I see you a moment?

930
01:15:12,497 --> 01:15:13,580
All right.

931
01:15:13,999 --> 01:15:16,334
<i>I mean, she should be here
by now, shouldn't she?</i>

932
01:15:16,334 --> 01:15:17,998
<i>Even if Hector didn't show up?</i>

933
01:15:18,003 --> 01:15:19,415
Your sister's dead.

934
01:15:22,505 --> 01:15:24,841
What?

935
01:15:24,842 --> 01:15:27,962
I realize this comes
as a shock,

936
01:15:27,970 --> 01:15:29,428
<i>but she had been exposed,</i>

937
01:15:29,429 --> 01:15:32,264
<i>and in 48 hours
she would have died anyway.</i>

938
01:15:32,265 --> 01:15:35,305
It was quite painless
I can assure you.

939
01:15:42,982 --> 01:15:45,477
My, you both have nice,
strong hearts.

940
01:15:45,486 --> 01:15:46,853
Are we gonna get shots?

941
01:15:47,153 --> 01:15:50,444
No, no shots, I promise.

942
01:15:51,491 --> 01:15:53,529
- Audrey?
- Not back yet.

943
01:15:53,533 --> 01:15:55,903
Listen, we may have a situation
on our hands here.

944
01:15:55,911 --> 01:15:58,451
I can't locate Rogers
anyplace in the compound.

945
01:15:58,455 --> 01:16:00,494
<i>Shi...</i>

946
01:16:00,499 --> 01:16:02,242
I can't rule out the possibility

947
01:16:02,250 --> 01:16:04,459
that he may already
have gone into transition.

948
01:16:07,713 --> 01:16:10,001
We can't wait for Audrey.

949
01:16:10,006 --> 01:16:12,592
You're gonna have to start with
the children and that one in there.

950
01:16:12,593 --> 01:16:14,460
We need blood
to develop the serum.

951
01:16:15,428 --> 01:16:17,261
We don't have enough
for everyone.

952
01:16:19,556 --> 01:16:21,391
We're not robots, Doctor.

953
01:16:21,392 --> 01:16:23,760
We're not all gonna fall over
at one time.

954
01:16:23,769 --> 01:16:26,013
Some of us
will last a little longer

955
01:16:26,021 --> 01:16:29,107
while others of us
have more immediate need.

956
01:16:29,107 --> 01:16:31,850
You're smart.
You can figure that out.

957
01:16:31,859 --> 01:16:35,480
<i>Psychology? not an exact
science, but my God, man,</i>

958
01:16:35,488 --> 01:16:37,651
<i>anybody can add two and two!</i>

959
01:16:41,827 --> 01:16:44,071
<i>I'm very sorry
about your sister.</i>

960
01:16:44,079 --> 01:16:46,198
It's a tragedy.

961
01:16:46,206 --> 01:16:48,665
It, uh, it truly is.

962
01:16:55,673 --> 01:17:00,008
And I can understand your hostility,
but no matter how upset you are,

963
01:17:00,008 --> 01:17:03,469
breaking an expensive piece
of equipment won't solve anything.

964
01:17:03,470 --> 01:17:06,636
I mean,
striking out at inanimate objects

965
01:17:06,641 --> 01:17:08,599
<i>is really quite childish.</i>

966
01:17:08,600 --> 01:17:10,934
Even you should be able
to realize that.

967
01:17:13,980 --> 01:17:15,223
Jerk.

968
01:17:43,798 --> 01:17:46,258
Howdy, partner.
How you doin'?

969
01:17:47,593 --> 01:17:50,179
- Who are you?
- My names Hec.

970
01:17:51,179 --> 01:17:52,638
Hec Gomez.

971
01:17:54,640 --> 01:17:57,101
Hey, them's real fine duds
you got there.

972
01:17:57,102 --> 01:17:59,436
<i>You a Maytag repairman?</i>

973
01:17:59,437 --> 01:18:00,850
How'd you find this place?

974
01:18:02,231 --> 01:18:05,646
Well, uh, this lady
back in L.A. sent me.

975
01:18:05,650 --> 01:18:08,110
Hey, you been to L.A. lately?

976
01:18:08,111 --> 01:18:09,900
It's cleaned out, man,
I'm tellin' ya.

977
01:18:09,905 --> 01:18:12,319
Hey, come here,
I wanna show you somethin'.

978
01:18:12,324 --> 01:18:13,282
Come on.

979
01:18:15,576 --> 01:18:19,197
Hey, you know how the Harbor Freeway's
always bumper to bumper?

980
01:18:19,204 --> 01:18:21,617
Well, you can go 150 miles
an hour if you want to.

981
01:18:22,166 --> 01:18:24,205
Me and this baby.

982
01:18:24,209 --> 01:18:27,328
We go through them freeways
like turkey crap through a tin horn.

983
01:18:33,134 --> 01:18:34,251
Hey, uh...

984
01:18:37,596 --> 01:18:38,929
You like girls?

985
01:18:40,724 --> 01:18:41,886
Look in here.

986
01:18:47,563 --> 01:18:50,102
- She's dead.
- She ain't dead.

987
01:18:50,106 --> 01:18:52,566
See, this lady shot her up
with sodium pentothal

988
01:18:52,567 --> 01:18:54,356
and make this fella think
she was dead.

989
01:18:54,653 --> 01:18:55,770
Uh!

990
01:18:58,072 --> 01:19:01,487
So you wouldn't suck
her blood out, you asshole.

991
01:19:05,119 --> 01:19:06,658
Son of a bitch!

992
01:19:09,624 --> 01:19:10,787
Shit!

993
01:19:21,093 --> 01:19:23,006
<i>Excuse me, everyone.</i>

994
01:19:23,010 --> 01:19:25,095
<i>I'm afraid our adolescent
guest has escaped.</i>

