01:19:25,972 --> 01:19:28,012
She's quite hostile.

996
01:19:28,016 --> 01:19:30,429
She may have already
gone topside, so please,

997
01:19:30,434 --> 01:19:32,643
<i>take a moment
to look around you.</i>

998
01:19:55,956 --> 01:19:57,621
Check those rooms
and I'll check this one.

999
01:21:56,271 --> 01:21:57,559
Let's go.

1000
01:22:05,113 --> 01:22:07,231
Everything's under control.

1001
01:22:07,239 --> 01:22:08,402
Good.

1002
01:22:37,891 --> 01:22:39,759
You said no shots.

1003
01:22:39,768 --> 01:22:41,351
This isn't a shot, sweetheart.

1004
01:22:41,352 --> 01:22:43,392
It'll just--

1005
01:22:43,397 --> 01:22:47,109
You'll just giggle and then
you'll feel a little sleepy.

1006
01:22:47,109 --> 01:22:48,442
That's right.

1007
01:22:48,442 --> 01:22:50,935
And when you wake up,
do you know where you'll be?

1008
01:22:50,944 --> 01:22:54,360
- Where?
- With Santa Claus at the North Pole.

1009
01:22:54,364 --> 01:22:58,531
In fact, you'll live with Santa Claus
for the rest of your life.

1010
01:22:58,535 --> 01:23:01,074
Hey, there's no such thing
as Santa Claus.

1011
01:23:01,078 --> 01:23:02,412
<i>What?</i>

1012
01:23:03,331 --> 01:23:05,119
You don't believe in Santa?

1013
01:23:24,349 --> 01:23:26,342
Life support systems.

1014
01:23:28,019 --> 01:23:29,388
Wilson, come with me.

1015
01:23:30,606 --> 01:23:32,064
- Keep an eye on her.
- Right.

1016
01:23:32,064 --> 01:23:34,399
<i>Now, Wilson!</i>

1017
01:23:34,400 --> 01:23:36,940
<i>Forget the door!
Turn off the alarm!</i>

1018
01:23:40,907 --> 01:23:41,989
Uh!

1019
01:23:52,416 --> 01:23:54,330
<i>I don't know.</i>

1020
01:23:54,335 --> 01:23:57,829
<i>My parents told me never
to breathe anything from strangers.</i>

1021
01:23:57,837 --> 01:23:58,920
Hey!

1022
01:24:00,924 --> 01:24:02,041
Get your hands up.

1023
01:24:08,846 --> 01:24:10,090
What are you guys doing?

1024
01:24:10,098 --> 01:24:11,682
They said if we breathe this,

1025
01:24:11,683 --> 01:24:15,473
we could go to the North Pole
and see Santa Claus.

1026
01:24:15,478 --> 01:24:17,267
That's so sick.

1027
01:24:17,271 --> 01:24:18,309
Hey!

1028
01:24:18,314 --> 01:24:19,806
Holy shit!

1029
01:24:19,814 --> 01:24:21,183
- Whoa.
- Sam?

1030
01:24:21,192 --> 01:24:22,434
I give, I give.

1031
01:24:22,984 --> 01:24:24,569
They said you were dead.

1032
01:24:24,570 --> 01:24:27,655
They were exaggerating totally.

1033
01:24:27,656 --> 01:24:30,115
- Hey, that's a great outfit.
- Thanks.

1034
01:24:30,115 --> 01:24:31,609
<i>Is that guy
in the hallway dead?</i>

1035
01:24:33,118 --> 01:24:34,452
Don't.

1036
01:24:45,630 --> 01:24:46,793
Well?

1037
01:24:51,176 --> 01:24:54,046
You can give up
if you want to, Wilson.

1038
01:24:57,266 --> 01:24:59,930
But we still have
the two children and that girl.

1039
01:25:02,019 --> 01:25:03,181
I forgot my football.

1040
01:25:03,186 --> 01:25:04,304
We'll get you another football.

1041
01:25:04,313 --> 01:25:05,805
We'll get you a stadium.

1042
01:25:08,693 --> 01:25:09,809
Now.

1043
01:25:22,162 --> 01:25:24,325
Get everybody topside.
Now!

1044
01:25:24,330 --> 01:25:25,288
What about them?

1045
01:25:26,082 --> 01:25:27,700
Screw them.

1046
01:25:34,006 --> 01:25:36,921
<i>Okay, kids, going up.</i>

1047
01:25:36,925 --> 01:25:38,964
Put your hands down, kids.

1048
01:25:39,428 --> 01:25:41,342
God, don't be so stupid.

1049
01:25:53,815 --> 01:25:56,150
- Come on, kids!
- Who are the kids?

1050
01:25:56,151 --> 01:25:57,609
- I'm Brian.
- I'm Sarah.

1051
01:25:57,609 --> 01:25:59,819
Yeah, and I'm Aunt Reg
and that's Aunt Sam

1052
01:25:59,820 --> 01:26:01,313
and that's Uncle Hector.

1053
01:26:01,322 --> 01:26:02,486
Can I have my bunny?

1054
01:26:02,490 --> 01:26:05,154
In a minute.
Beat feet, Uncle Hector.

1055
01:26:05,159 --> 01:26:06,446
Uncle Hector?

1056
01:26:06,451 --> 01:26:08,410
<i>Hey, it's my bunny, you know?</i>

1057
01:26:16,752 --> 01:26:17,790
Where have you been?

1058
01:26:17,794 --> 01:26:19,037
<i>Can we change this?</i>

1059
01:26:19,046 --> 01:26:20,710
Arranging a hotfoot
for your friends.

1060
01:26:20,714 --> 01:26:22,378
I really hate this music.

1061
01:26:22,382 --> 01:26:23,749
Give me a break!

1062
01:26:26,470 --> 01:26:27,507
What are you doing?

1063
01:26:27,511 --> 01:26:31,256
I'm not kidding,
I get car sick without my bunny.

1064
01:26:31,264 --> 01:26:33,599
Come on, Reg,
give the kid the bunny.

1065
01:26:33,600 --> 01:26:35,515
We've stopped,
why have we stopped?

1066
01:26:35,519 --> 01:26:38,558
- Son of a--
- Don't shoot them, you idiot.

1067
01:26:38,563 --> 01:26:41,352
Okay, kids, cover your eyes
for Uncle Hector.

1068
01:26:44,401 --> 01:26:46,190
Hey!

1069
01:26:46,195 --> 01:26:47,529
Think tank, huh?

1070
01:26:47,529 --> 01:26:50,273
Uh, look, couldn't
we just like, leave?

1071
01:26:50,282 --> 01:26:51,398
Think over this!

1072
01:26:53,159 --> 01:26:54,652
We can get them.

1073
01:26:54,660 --> 01:26:57,700
<i>- Hey, we'll be taking off now.
- We have to get them.</i>

1074
01:26:57,705 --> 01:27:00,699
Look us up at Chasen's.
Uh, we'll party down, huh?

1075
01:27:00,707 --> 01:27:02,496
- Come on.
- Come on, come on, this is fun.

1076
01:27:04,126 --> 01:27:06,587
The kids would like to say good-bye,
it's been fun.

1077
01:27:06,588 --> 01:27:08,456
Hope to see you around
real soon.

1078
01:27:11,217 --> 01:27:12,710
Is that gasoline I smell?

1079
01:27:17,764 --> 01:27:19,098
<i>Wait, wait, don't, don't!</i>

1080
01:27:43,454 --> 01:27:45,071
Wow.

1081
01:27:45,080 --> 01:27:46,288
All right, Hector.

1082
01:28:01,761 --> 01:28:03,380
Let go of her!
Leave her alone!

1083
01:28:06,516 --> 01:28:07,804
Hector!

1084
01:28:12,729 --> 01:28:15,394
<i>- Reggie.
- It's all right.</i>

1085
01:28:15,399 --> 01:28:18,313
<i>It's all right. It's okay.</i>

1086
01:28:19,485 --> 01:28:20,853
<i>I got you.</i>

1087
01:28:20,862 --> 01:28:22,355
<i>It's all right.</i>

1088
01:28:22,363 --> 01:28:24,027
<i>It's okay.</i>

1089
01:28:24,031 --> 01:28:25,365
<i>I got you.</i>

1090
01:28:25,366 --> 01:28:26,984
Shhh.

1091
01:29:08,946 --> 01:29:11,065
<i>Okay, kids, smile, come on.</i>

1092
01:29:13,325 --> 01:29:16,320
Oh, don't-- God, you're so cute!
You're just so cute-- wait.

1093
01:29:17,370 --> 01:29:19,454
Mr. Bunny needs to be
in this picture too.

1094
01:29:19,455 --> 01:29:21,074
So, okay, that's great.

1095
01:29:21,082 --> 01:29:22,369
Can I take this jacket off?

1096
01:29:22,374 --> 01:29:23,867
- It itches.
- No, you can't.

1097
01:29:23,876 --> 01:29:25,743
I just want to take
another picture, all right?

1098
01:29:25,752 --> 01:29:26,995
- Please?
- No.

1099
01:29:27,004 --> 01:29:28,292
Now,
you just hold on to that.

1100
01:29:28,297 --> 01:29:29,789
- Stay there. Okay, perfect.
- Oh, brother.

1101
01:29:29,797 --> 01:29:31,883
<i>There's still
a few zombies around.</i>

1102
01:29:31,884 --> 01:29:34,673
<i>Don't slouch.
And Sarah--</i>

1103
01:29:34,677 --> 01:29:35,793
Hold that.

1104
01:29:37,554 --> 01:29:38,923
Smile.

1105
01:29:41,099 --> 01:29:42,308
<i>Did the flash go off?</i>

1106
01:29:42,310 --> 01:29:44,268
<i>Can't tell on these things.</i>

1107
01:29:44,269 --> 01:29:46,557
Hey, if you're gonna throw
those guns away,

1108
01:29:46,562 --> 01:29:47,850
<i>can I have one?</i>

1109
01:29:51,567 --> 01:29:52,775
Don't look at me.

1110
01:29:52,777 --> 01:29:54,441
I mean, I don't know
where she gets that stuff.

1111
01:29:58,532 --> 01:30:00,446
<i>Smile, Hec.</i>

1112
01:30:03,160 --> 01:30:04,369
Handsome.

1113
01:30:06,247 --> 01:30:08,411
Maybe I could be
a nun or something.

1114
01:30:09,166 --> 01:30:11,376
Ooh,
I just love these pictures.

1115
01:30:11,669 --> 01:30:13,627
You've only taken
about 30 of 'em.

1116
01:30:13,628 --> 01:30:14,917
You know, we're going to need
some more film soon.

1117
01:30:14,922 --> 01:30:16,005
- Let me straighten your tie.
- Okay.

1118
01:30:17,340 --> 01:30:19,549
God, they look
like the Brady Bunch.

1119
01:30:21,134 --> 01:30:22,843
What are you waiting for?

1120
01:30:23,387 --> 01:30:24,846
Can I see 'em?

1121
01:30:24,846 --> 01:30:26,680
We're waiting
for the light to change.

1122
01:30:26,682 --> 01:30:28,266
We do not cross
against the light.

1123
01:30:32,103 --> 01:30:34,392
Are you nuts,
Auntie Regina?

1124
01:30:35,147 --> 01:30:38,938
You may as well
face the facts, Samantha.

1125
01:30:38,943 --> 01:30:42,858
The whole burden of civilization
has fallen upon us.

1126
01:30:45,282 --> 01:30:46,899
What's that supposed to mean?

1127
01:30:48,827 --> 01:30:51,912
It means we do not cross
against the light.

1128
01:30:54,038 --> 01:30:56,203
That's totally stupid!

1129
01:30:56,208 --> 01:30:57,700
There's nobody here!

1130
01:30:57,709 --> 01:31:00,954
See, we're talking ghost town!

1131
01:31:09,387 --> 01:31:10,469
See what happens.

1132
01:31:16,559 --> 01:31:20,179
God, I'm sorry, but you shouldn't cross
against the light like that.

1133
01:31:23,107 --> 01:31:25,350
Hey, you guys are
survivors too, huh?

1134
01:31:28,528 --> 01:31:31,067
- What?
- Nothin'.

1135
01:31:31,071 --> 01:31:32,030
Great car.

1136
01:31:32,574 --> 01:31:34,987
Thanks, I have 23 of them.
You want to go for a ride?

1137
01:31:34,992 --> 01:31:37,030
More than you know.

1138
01:31:40,705 --> 01:31:42,244
We don't know anything
about this guy.

1139
01:31:43,292 --> 01:31:44,499
Where's he from?

1140
01:31:44,500 --> 01:31:45,788
What's his name?

1141
01:31:45,793 --> 01:31:48,002
- What's your name.
- Danny Mason Keener.

1142
01:31:48,795 --> 01:31:50,584
<i>Danny Mason Keener, okay?</i>

1143
01:31:52,507 --> 01:31:55,968
Yeah, all right, well, just be back
by midnight, okay?

1144
01:31:55,969 --> 01:31:57,506
Midnight?

1145
01:31:57,511 --> 01:32:00,598
The burden of civilization
is on us, okay?

1146
01:32:00,599 --> 01:32:02,307
Oh, yeah.

1147
01:32:02,308 --> 01:32:03,846
Bitchin', isn't it?

